  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through various mechanisms, including:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Establishing legal frameworks to investigate and prosecute\n\n2. Investigative Techniques\n- Financial forensic analysis\n- Tracing complex financial transactions\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Using advanced technology and data analytics\n\n3. International Cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated investigations across jurisdictions\n\n4. Prosecution Strategies\n- Targeting financial infrastructure\n- Seizing assets\n- Pursuing criminal charges against individuals involved\n\n5. Regulatory Oversight\n- Monitoring financial institutions\n- Imposing strict compliance requirements\n- Implementing penalties for non-compliance\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and investigative strategies.",
